			The code is dead simple, each pixel's color values are generated by a function of the x and y coordinates.
			Some of the plots ended up being far more interesting than I expected so I wanted to share some of the images and code, as well as a generator so you can play and make your own.
		</p>
		<p>
			I'll try for useful next week<sup>*</sup>
			<span style="font-size:xx-small; float:right;">* Almost certainly a lie</span>
		</p>
	</div>
	<div class="tags"><span>JustForFun</span><span>ASP.Net MVC</span><span>SQL</span><span>Tutorials</span></div>
</div>

